        "timestamp": "2021-02-25 14:49:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n1. I'm not sure if this cli is even used? Sylvain mentioned it is in maintenance mode and should be removed in the future\n\n2. if it would be used, there is a lot that could be improved:\nsudo should not be installed and stuff should run as normal user (seccom req since frankfurt from what I've found on wiki)\nswitch to alpine would be nice - (to lessen deployment footprint) preferrably to integration:8.0.0 (which will give additional benefits in the future)\nchmod 777 for whole /usr/local shouldnt be here, change perms for what is needed\nIt might be a better idea to have different dockers for each mode (so it has just the ports it needs open)",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
